(7, 'Alameda County may receive new COVID-19 accommodation orders if ICU capacity declines or soon', 1, '&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Update, 9 p.m.&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Dare2BWell/status/1334668585373855747&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;Alameda County&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;Health officials a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.berkeleyside.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/AlamedaCountyPublicHealthshelterathomeorderDec32020.pdf&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;Report&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;If social outreach worsens and ICU capacity begins to decline, they may be able to execute shelter-at-home orders sooner than the state needs. The latest numbers are 33%, according to the county&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://covid-19.acgov.org/data.page&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;Data on hospitalization.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;page&quot; title=&quot;Page 1&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;layoutArea&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;column&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;Although Alameda County&rsquo;s ICU capacity currently exceeds 15%, if this situation worsens, we will have to enforce restrictions on staying in the state before meeting the Bay Area area gate to protect the availability of ICU beds and save lives,&rdquo; officials said.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Original story:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;With COVID-19 cases rising dramatically across the state, Govin Gavin NewSom today announced a new shelter-order, which is expected to take effect in Alameda County later this month if the ICU hospital capacity for the Bay Area is less than 15%.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://covid19.ca.gov/stay-home-except-for-essential-needs/#regional&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;New guidelines&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;Divide the state into five areas based on mutual hospital assistance: Northern California, Greater Sacramento, Bay Area &ndash; including Berkeley and Alameda County &ndash; San Joaquin Valley and Southern California.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Bay Area is the best of the regions, all of which are expected to drop to 15% earlier this month, but NewSom said local ICU capacity could drop below the limit in the Bay Area after a few days. If that happens the following rules will apply:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 18px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; list-style: none; position: relative;&quot;&gt;No meetings with people outside your home.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 18px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; list-style: none; position: relative;&quot;&gt;Personal care services such as liquor stores, wineries, hair salons and barbershops and playgrounds will be closed.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 18px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; list-style: none; position: relative;&quot;&gt;Schools that are already open can remain open, as well as restaurants with critical infrastructure, 20% capacity retail and carry and supply.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;bside-ad-med-rectangle-after-paragraph-02 cta-inline signup-daily-briefing&quot; id=&quot;bside-ad-219586056&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;cta-inline-content&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;margin: 0em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Regions must adhere to the regulations for at least three weeks, during which time the government will monitor social exchange and trend taxes for the coming weeks. Once the requirements are met and the restrictions are lifted, the districts will return to their tiers&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://covid19.ca.gov/safer-economy/&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;State COVID Blueprint.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;That variation system&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.berkeleyside.com/2020/07/15/outdoor-dining-allowed-berkeley-state-approval&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;Previously Berkeley and Alameda County were allowed to impose lower regulatory guidelines&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;No longer in effect, and the city and district must follow state rules and regulations if they are to be passed. However, the district and the city have the ability to impose strict rules.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Newsom announced on Thursday that all essential travel will be banned statewide as it continues to rise.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pullquote&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;We don&rsquo;t expect to do this again, but we all need to move forward.&rdquo; &ndash; Government Newsom&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;There is light at the end of the tunnel, and we are a few months away from seeing real progress with vaccines, real distribution, real access, real availability,&rdquo; Newsom said, adding that the third wave was the &ldquo;final rise&rdquo; of the epidemic. &ldquo;We don&rsquo;t expect to do this again, but we should all make progress.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The government has made it a priority to provide more than 320,000 vaccines&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sacbee.com/news/politics-government/capitol-alert/article247512730.html&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;Three layers&lt;/a&gt;, Is expected to start receiving this month. This includes hospitals, health workers and other vulnerable populations in prisons. Newsom said orders for the vaccinated areas will begin on Friday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;On November 19, the government received a pass&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cdph.ca.gov/Programs/CID/DCDC/Pages/COVID-19/limited-stay-at-home-order.aspx&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;Limited order at home&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;Non-essential businesses must be closed every day from 10pm to 5am every day until December 21st. The new rules are in response to the highest number in the state since the onset of the epidemic, with an average of nearly 15,000 cases a day.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;margin: 0em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; clear: both;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.haveeru.com.mv/southwest-is-expanding-from-uniteds-houston-and-chicago-hubs/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; class=&quot;ubdbd7e09dbf58528b0e255cf704001d3&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30); width: 796px; display: block; font-weight: 700; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 250ms ease 0s; padding-top: 1em !important; padding-bottom: 1em !important; border: 0px !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ctaText&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: inherit;&quot;&gt;READ&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;postTitle&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: inherit; text-decoration-line: underline !important;&quot;&gt;Southwest is expanding from United&amp;#x2019;s Houston and Chicago hubs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The effects of the Thanksgiving holiday are not included in the current numbers. One month ago, there were 14 deaths a day in California. Currently, the daily death rate in the state is 113 deaths per day.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Numbers in Alameda County also saw a spike, but recent daily case records were at least partly due&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.berkeleyside.com/2020/11/25/how-did-200-racetrack-workers-at-golden-gate-fields-get-covid-19&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;The Golden Gate Fields race erupted&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;On the border of Albany and Berkeley. More than 200 workers were infected with the virus there, and more than 95% of cases were reported as asymptomatic.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;There are currently nine cases per 100,000 residents in Alameda County, which is adjusted to test counts in the county, with an overall test positive of 3.6%. Since the onset of the epidemic, 520 people have died at the district level.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The number of hospital admissions has increased to 157 in the last few weeks and to 57 in the ICU, up from 213 hospital admissions and 62 in the ICU in July. But hospital admissions have increased rapidly in the current upsurge. The county now has 85 ICU beds (one area of ​​total regional availability), which is 30% of its total.&lt;/p&gt;											', '1607105400_th.png', 1, '2020-12-04 10:10:59', '2020-12-04 10:10:59'),
(8, 'We are all alone: ​​Oxford study says chances of brilliant living elsewhere are slim', 4, '&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;According to a new study from Oxford University, their statistical opportunities for other intelligent life in the universe are &ldquo;exceptionally rare.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;In the study, scientists at Oxford&rsquo;s Future Humanitarian Institute believe that as life on Earth evolves, in many cases it depends on a series of &ldquo;revolutionary changes&rdquo;. Given how late intelligent life evolved on this planet, the chances of similar advances occurring on other planets, before they could no longer sustain life, were not very likely, they said.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;It took about 4.5 billion years of continuous evolution, resulting in a brilliant life on Earth,&rdquo; they wrote.&amp;nbsp;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.liebertpub.com/doi/10.1089/ast.2019.2149&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;Paper published last month.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&ldquo;In another billion years, the rising light of the sun will make the earth uninhabitable for complex life.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;newsletter-promo&quot; style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Receive the times of the daily edition of Israel by email and never miss our best stories&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;Along with the scattering time of major evolutionary changes and reliable predecessors, it can be concluded that the expected transition times may be longer than the lifespan of the Earth, perhaps by several commands,&rdquo; he wrote. &ldquo;In turn, this suggests that intelligent life may be exceptionally rare.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;To reach their results, the scientist looked at statistical models to determine the probability that the sequence of evolutionary changes that took place on Earth might occur elsewhere.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;attachment_2442311&quot; class=&quot;wp-caption alignnone&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px 0px 1px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(247, 247, 247); overflow-wrap: break-word; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em;&quot;&gt;This image, taken by NASA, is taken from the International Space Station on Sunday, July 5, 2020, on the eastern horizon above the Earth, Walmot Nouvis. (Via NASA AP)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&ldquo;We used the assumption that what happened on Earth was common to what was happening on other planets &ndash; not just the right times, but there are some tricky steps that need to be taken continuously to create intelligent viewers,&rdquo; said Anders Sandberg of Oxford.&amp;nbsp;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-9000797/Scientists-say-intelligent-life-planets-exceptionally-rare.html&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(206, 24, 30);&quot;&gt;Daily Mail&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;											', '1607105460_sgdf.jpg', 1, '2020-12-04 10:11:54', '2020-12-04 10:11:54'),
(9, 'macOS Big Sur Review: New and familiar mix', 5, '&lt;h3 style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 22px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-weight: 700; font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.35;&quot;&gt;News and maps&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;If you use both an iPhone and a Mac, Messaging is one of the most important apps you have on both devices. Fortunately, with Big Source, the news experience is almost identical on the sites. iOS 14 brings new features such as in-line responses, the ability to track conversations, chat group chat tips and custom images, and advanced search capabilities &ndash; all of which are on the big screen. For years Apple has been bringing Mac to iOS messages, including a built-in GIF search, emoji stickers and &ldquo;message effects&rdquo; (such as sending a message with a confetti or fireworks cloud). So if a friend sends a message with a laser effect from their phone, you will not see the monotonous text description &ldquo;sent with lasers&rdquo; on your Mac. It&rsquo;s the little things.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.8em; color: rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family: Roboto, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The Map app has also received some major updates, bringing it back online with what you see on iOS. Google Maps fans won&rsquo;t worry about these changes, but Apple Maps on the iPhone is actually much better these days (at least in the US). But, like the news, the maps on the Mac have not seen many of the features that Apple has added to its iOS app over the years. Now, they are in perfect symmetry. The biggest advantage is that any &ldquo;guide&rdquo; you create on your phone (basically a list of places you save) is also available on the Mac. Previously, maps only allowed you to add places to a &ldquo;Favorites&rdquo; list, but having multiple lists was very natural. That way, you can save the places you want to visit on vacation (when we are allowed to travel again,&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;&quot;&gt;Sigh&lt;/em&gt;) Separately from your favorite local places.&lt;/p&gt;											', '1607105520_erger.jpeg', 1, '2020-12-04 10:12:46', '2020-12-04 10:12:46'),
